This paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms in mobile health, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on personalization, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of data from other users to improve personalization, which involves data analysis and statistics (cs.CY) as well as machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses a live clinical trial, which involves the application of technology in a real-world setting (cs.SI).
